    • Method Detail

      • put

        void put(byte[] objectId,
         byte[] value,
         byte[] metadata)
        Put value in the local plasma store with object ID objectId.
        Parameters:
        objectId - The object ID of the value to be put.
        value - The value to put in the object store.
        metadata - encodes whatever metadata the user wishes to encode.

      • get

        default byte[] get(byte[] objectId,
                   int timeoutMs,
                   boolean isMetadata)
        Create a buffer from the PlasmaStore based on the objectId.
        Parameters:
        objectId - The object ID used to identify the object.
        timeoutMs - The number of milliseconds that the get call should block before timing out and returning. Pass -1 if the call should block and 0 if the call should return immediately.
        isMetadata - false if get data, otherwise get metadata.
        Returns:
        A PlasmaBuffer wrapping the object.

      • get

        List<byte[]> get(byte[][] objectIds,
                 int timeoutMs,
                 boolean isMetadata)
        Create buffers from the PlasmaStore based on objectIds.
        Parameters:
        objectIds - List of object IDs used to identify some objects.
        timeoutMs - The number of milliseconds that the get call should block before timing out and returning. Pass -1 if the call should block and 0 if the call should return immediately.
        isMetadata - false if get data, otherwise get metadata.
        Returns:
        List of PlasmaBuffers wrapping objects.

      • wait

        List<byte[]> wait(byte[][] objectIds,
                  int timeoutMs,
                  int numReturns)
        Wait until numReturns objects in objectIds are ready.
        Parameters:
        objectIds - List of object IDs to wait for.
        timeoutMs - Return to the caller after timeoutMs milliseconds.
        numReturns - We are waiting for this number of objects to be ready.
        Returns:
        List of object IDs that are ready

      • hash

        byte[] hash(byte[] objectId)
        Compute the hash of an object in the object store.
        Parameters:
        objectId - The object ID used to identify the object.
        Returns:
        A digest byte array contains object's SHA256 hash. null means that the object isn't in the object store.
